I’m so pumped to announce @blackdaggerbooks is putting out a book of my paintings for their February release! They have a really cool subscription service where you receive a book a month and they have had some killer artists they’ve worked with. I’m really honored they asked a joker like me! Please go to their page and support them, this whole thing has been wildly helpful for me and I’ve got plenty of stuff in the book I’ve never shared so there will be stuff you’ve never seen. Thank you guys! I appreciate this so much!
Been doing some classic sailor designs for Pedro who is getting these to commemorate his career in the navy. It’s a lot of fun working on you bro! Thank you for everything you’ve gotten so far.
Cover up for Zack last night - thanks a lot bro, I had a great time tattooing this for you.

It’s official, the book is out - Go to @blackdaggerbooks to get your copy if you haven’t subscribed to them. I hope you like it, there’s some paintings in there I’ll never share online.  Please go and support them, they get great artists every month, it’s really worth it.

I have a hard time thinking of new ideas when I’ve been painting so much. I’ve done over 30 paintings since March, I’m not burnt out but I start to run out of inspiration. I want to paint but start to get bored and paint stuff I’m not sure anyone else actually likes hahaha. I want to tattoo these designs so I always have other people in mind even if I’m just painting something for myself.
Anyone else feel this way? Like you can never really let go of considering what people want to buy?
I did a painting trade with @jgettlershred - first one is the one he did swipe for mine. Thanks a lot man! I love it! Give him a follow if you don’t already, his art is killer.
